The provincial leaders will now meet with the party&#8217;s national working committee on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - The African National Congress (ANC) has confirmed that its national working committee will meet with the party s KwaZulu-Natal leaders to reflect on a High Court s judgment declaring the province s 2015 elective conference unlawful.On Wednesday, the provincial party s leagues announced that they intend appealing that judgment.Through its leagues, the ANC in KwaZulu-Natal stopped just short of telling the ANC s national executive committee to back off after the mother body s Zizi Kodwa said the provincial party had no authority to decide what it does next, without consulting the NEC.The provincial leaders will now meet with the party s national working committee on Friday.ANC KZN spokesperson Mdumiseni Ntuli says: The chairperson meeting is to reflect on the judgment handed down by the Pietermaritzburg High Court. Although the provincial party has already decided to appeal the judgment without the blessing of the NEC, Ntuli says the meeting on Friday will be used to determine the way forward.